23/03/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling coalition, consisting of the Democratic Party (DP) and the Republican Party (RP), signed a pre-election agreement ahead of the June parliamentary elections Saturday (March 21st). Under the agreement, both parties will commit to focusing all resources and efforts on winning the elections. "I believe this coalition contributes to the country's development and integration," Prime Minister Sali Berisha, the DP leader, said. RP leader Fatmir Mediu said the agreement confirms the coalition's stability. (Shekulli, Shqip, Gazeta Shqiptare, Balkan Web - 21/03/09) 
